The paper discusses the complexity of regular languages represented by their minimal deterministic finite automata, which is a topic in formal language theory (FL). The paper also considers the size of syntactic semigroups, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (DM). The study of complexity measures for regular language operations involves computational complexity (CC) and the use of algorithms. The paper also discusses convexity, which is a topic in both logic (LO) and information theory (IT).
